        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 2:51PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 251 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Las Vegas, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Las Vegas and Storrie Lake State Park.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 343 and 352.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 1 and 8.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
